Governor Abdulrahman Abdulrazaq of Kwara State has approved the appointments of board members for seven government parastatals in the state. They are, the Kwara Road Maintenance Agency; Kwara Signage Agency; Rural Water Supply and Sanitation Programme, (RUWSSA); and Rural Electrification. Others include College of Arabic and Islamic Studies, (CAILS); Kwara Environmental Agency, (KWEPA); and Arts and Culture. A statement by the governor’s spokesman, Rafiu Ajakaye in Ilorin, said ” The governor approved the appointments based on recommendations from various stakeholders in the state.” He added that many other board appointments are in the works.